==Abstract==

This NEP describes a URI standard for transfer of NEO native assets, as well as smart contracts deployed on chain.  

==Motivation==

Currently, there is no standard URI for NEO clients to consume. Bitcoin implements a URI standard so that clicking links or scanning QR codes can easily implement a bitcoin payment. Similarly the transfer of native assets on the NEO chain should be just as simple.

However since NEO also implements NEP-5 tokens, as well as generic smart contracts. Transfer of NEP-5 tokens should be equally easy to perform. Lastly, generic smart contracts should be able to be invoked on scanning of QR or clicking of a link. This allows wallet developers to consume the URI in an easy way

==Specification==

===Native Asset Transfer===

A Native asset transfer would have the following URI. It describes the reciever address, assetID, and additional attributes that will be sent with the transaction. The attributes are presented in raw hex data.

```NEO:<address>[?assetID=<assetID>][?attributes=<key=value>][?amount=<amount>]```

